# Pages in the Help: namespace  

The **Help: namespace** gathers a collection of “how‑to” and informational pages whose titles all begin with the prefix **Help:**, such as **[Help:Link](/Help:Link)**. These pages are designed to assist users in navigating Wikipedia’s encyclopedic content, its editing tools, and the underlying software. Some articles in this namespace are aimed at readers of the encyclopedia, while others are geared toward editors—whether they are newcomers or seasoned contributors. A significant portion of the material has been imported from **Meta‑Wiki**, the central wiki for Wikimedia projects, ensuring that the guidance reflects community‑wide consensus and best practices.  

The purpose of the Help namespace is to explain aspects of Wikipedia’s **norms**, **customs**, **technicalities**, and **practices**. Because these pages often embody the evolving **consensus** of the editing community, they may display varying degrees of **[consensus](/Wikipedia:Consensus)** and **[vetting](/Wikipedia:Consensus)**. In practice, this means that a Help page can be a concise reminder for one topic and an in‑depth guide for another, depending on how the community has refined its approach over time.  

> **Note:** The Help namespace is distinct from the **[Project namespace](/Wikipedia:Project_namespace)** (pages prefixed with *Wikipedia:*), although there is considerable overlap between the two. To manage this overlap, Wikipedia frequently employs **[redirects](/Help:Redirect)** and **[hatnotes](/Wikipedia:Hatnote)** that point users between the namespaces as needed. For a deeper dive into the relationship between Help and Project, see **[Help:About the help pages](/Help:About_the_help_pages)**.  

You can locate any Help page using the **[Special:Search](/Special:Search)** box located at the bottom of the page, which performs a full‑site search limited to the Help namespace.  

